WEBVTT

00:01.462 --> 00:02.623
PREVIOUSLY ON "REVENGE"...

00:02.623 --> 00:03.834
I AM CUTTING YOU

00:03.834 --> 00:06.047
AND YOUR CAMPAIGN
OFF FROM MY MONEY.

00:06.047 --> 00:07.968
NATALIE WATERS.
I'M NEW HERE.

00:07.968 --> 00:09.220
THERE'S PLENTY
OF SECRETS OUT THERE.

00:09.220 --> 00:11.092
EVERYONE HAS THEM.

00:11.092 --> 00:13.013
AND SOONER OR LATER,
I MAY EVEN LEARN YOURS.

00:13.013 --> 00:14.845
OH, I SUSPECT
IT WILL BE SOONER.

00:14.845 --> 00:17.558
MAN: I'm afraid there's been
a death in the family.

00:17.558 --> 00:19.480
I HEARD YOU GOT A MEDAL
FROM THE MAYOR TODAY.

00:19.480 --> 00:21.482
AND I LEFT IT,
ALONG WITH MY BADGE AND MY GUN,

00:21.482 --> 00:23.064
ON THE CHIEF'S DESK.
 WHY?

00:23.064 --> 00:25.146
TURNS OUT BEING A COP JUST
WASN'T THE RIGHT THING FOR ME.

00:25.146 --> 00:26.987
I KILLED AN FBI AGENT --
A BAD ONE, BUT STILL --

00:26.987 --> 00:28.279
AND WE LIED
ABOUT IT.

00:28.279 --> 00:30.201
I ASKED FOR EVIDENCE
ON EMILY.

00:30.201 --> 00:32.031
THEY'RE IN
ON THIS THING TOGETHER.

00:32.031 --> 00:33.074
USE THIS
TO TAKE THEM BOTH OUT.

00:33.074 --> 00:35.035
WELL,
THIS IS UNEXPECTED.

00:35.035 --> 00:36.707
YEAH, TO ME, TOO.

00:36.707 --> 00:38.159
SO...

00:46.217 --> 00:52.223
♪ PUSHIN' DOWN ON MY SHOULDERS ♪

00:52.223 --> 00:56.517
♪ AND EMPTYING MY LUNGS ♪

01:00.020 --> 01:01.982
I SHOULD GO.

01:01.982 --> 01:05.946
AND I SHOULD BE PLAYING
FIRST BASE FOR THE YANKEES.

01:05.946 --> 01:07.568
[ CHUCKLES ]

01:07.568 --> 01:09.950
WELL, I GUESS SOME THINGS
JUST AREN'T MEANT TO HAPPEN.

01:09.950 --> 01:11.692
BESIDES, I MEAN,
WHERE DO YOU HAVE TO BE

01:11.692 --> 01:13.404
THAT'S BETTER
THAN HERE?

01:13.404 --> 01:15.366
[ CHUCKLES ]
THAT'S A FAIR POINT.

01:15.366 --> 01:16.407
♪ AND YOU ESCAPE ME ♪

01:16.407 --> 01:17.658
IT'S JUST MY LIFE

01:17.658 --> 01:21.162
HASN'T EXACTLY
ALLOWED ME TO JUST...BE.

01:21.162 --> 01:23.544
♪ LIKE WORDS I NEVER ♪

01:23.544 --> 01:25.045
I TRULY CAN'T IMAGINE.

01:25.045 --> 01:26.757
♪ SHOULD HAVE SAID ♪

01:26.757 --> 01:28.048
THE PAST FEW YEARS,

01:28.048 --> 01:30.421
EVERYTHING I'VE DONE...

01:30.421 --> 01:32.092
ALL I'VE LOST...

01:32.092 --> 01:34.135
AND NOW...

01:34.135 --> 01:36.347
[ SIGHS ]

01:36.347 --> 01:37.888
♪ YOU'RE NEXT TO ME AGAIN ♪

01:39.180 --> 01:40.391
WE DON'T
HAVE TO DO THIS.

01:40.391 --> 01:41.642
DO WHAT?

01:41.642 --> 01:43.274
TALK ABOUT OUR PAST.

01:43.274 --> 01:44.485
♪ AND YOU ESCAPE ME ♪

01:44.485 --> 01:45.726
THEN HOW AM I GONNA I LEARN

01:45.726 --> 01:47.107
ALL OF YOUR DEEP,
DARK SECRETS?

01:47.107 --> 01:48.359
OH, I-I CAN ASSURE YOU,

01:48.359 --> 01:51.692
MY LIFE'S NOT NEARLY
THAT INTERESTING.

01:51.692 --> 01:54.365
AT LEAST IT WASN'T...
UNTIL NOW.

01:54.365 --> 01:57.158
♪ LIKE WORDS I NEVER
SHOULD HAVE SAID ♪

01:57.158 --> 01:58.579
AND I DON'T MEAN
TO BE THE GUY

01:58.579 --> 02:00.201
THAT SAYS THERE'S
SOMETHING ELSE

02:00.201 --> 02:02.042
WE COULD DO BESIDES TALK...

02:02.042 --> 02:03.294
♪ TO THE SURFACE ♪

02:03.294 --> 02:05.166
THERE'S DEFINITELY
SOMETHING ELSE

02:05.166 --> 02:06.627
WE COULD DO BESIDES TALK.

02:06.627 --> 02:09.340
♪ BUT ALL OF THE HEROES ♪

02:09.340 --> 02:13.093
♪ ARE DEAD ♪

02:15.346 --> 02:18.389
OOH!
IT'S STUNNING.

02:18.389 --> 02:19.640
[ LAUGHS ]

02:19.640 --> 02:21.472
MARGAUX...

02:21.472 --> 02:22.603
THANK YOU
FOR COMING.

02:22.603 --> 02:24.144
MY PLEASURE.

02:24.144 --> 02:26.146
BUT IT SEEMS
I'M WITHOUT MY CHECKBOOK.

02:26.146 --> 02:27.728
NO! OH, NO, NO, NO.

02:27.728 --> 02:29.069
IT'S NOT LIKE THAT.

02:29.069 --> 02:30.771
DUE TO SOME SAD NEWS,

02:30.771 --> 02:33.654
MY FINANCIAL CIRCUMSTANCE
IS ABOUT TO CHANGE.

02:33.654 --> 02:35.986
I RECEIVED A PHONE CALL
FROM AN ESTATE ATTORNEY,

02:35.986 --> 02:38.869
AND HE INFORMED ME
THAT DANIEL'S GRANDFATHER,

02:38.869 --> 02:40.331
EDWARD GRAYSON,
HAD PASSED AWAY.

02:40.331 --> 02:42.783
I'M SO SORRY.

02:42.783 --> 02:44.285
OH, HE WAS A GOOD MAN.

02:44.285 --> 02:46.957
THE READING OF THE WILL
IS LATER TODAY.

02:46.957 --> 02:49.750
THAT MUST BE
QUITE THE INHERITANCE.

02:49.750 --> 02:51.792
MM.

02:51.792 --> 02:53.884
EDWARD AND I ALWAYS HAD
A SPECIAL BOND.

02:53.884 --> 02:55.466
AND EVEN WHEN
CONRAD AND I DIVORCED,

02:55.466 --> 02:57.137
EDWARD REACHED OUT
TO ASSURE ME

02:57.137 --> 02:59.430
THAT I STILL HAD A PLACE
IN HIS HEART

02:59.430 --> 03:01.141
AND IN HIS WILL.

03:01.141 --> 03:04.064
HE WAS ALWAYS
THE PRACTICAL ONE.

03:04.064 --> 03:06.186
WHAT BETTER WAY
TO PAY TRIBUTE

03:06.186 --> 03:07.608
TO MR. GRAYSON'S MEMORY

03:07.608 --> 03:09.230
THAN TO USE
THE INHERITANCE

03:09.230 --> 03:11.772
FOR A PLACE HIS
GREAT-GRANDCHILD COULD ENJOY?

03:11.772 --> 03:13.113
WELL, THE REAL TRIBUTE

03:13.113 --> 03:15.986
WILL BE TO USE THE MONEY
TO HELP DANIEL'S FOUNDATION.

03:15.986 --> 03:18.409
MM.

03:18.409 --> 03:21.121
WHAT WOULD YOU THINK IF I WERE
TO TURN ONE OF THE BEDROOMS

03:21.121 --> 03:23.083
INTO A NURSERY FOR YOU
AND THE BABY?

03:23.083 --> 03:24.415
[ CHUCKLES ]

03:24.415 --> 03:25.916
YOU'RE TOO KIND,
VICTORIA.

03:25.916 --> 03:27.958
OH, I COULD SAY
THE SAME OF YOU

03:27.958 --> 03:29.830
FOR HAVING FOLLOWED
MY ADVICE.

03:29.830 --> 03:32.002
I SAW YOU
AT THE ROSS RECEPTION,

03:32.002 --> 03:33.464
AND FROM WHAT I INFERRED,

03:33.464 --> 03:36.046
YOU DROPPED YOUR VENDETTA
AGAINST EMILY

03:36.046 --> 03:38.759
IN YOUR PURSUIT TO CLEAR
DANIEL'S NAME.

03:41.221 --> 03:43.103
YOU NEEDN'T WORRY
ABOUT ANYTHING

03:43.103 --> 03:45.396
OTHER THAN PICKING OUT
A CRIB.

03:51.442 --> 03:53.023
YOU QUIT SO FAST
YOU DIDN'T HAVE TIME

03:53.023 --> 03:54.024
TO CLEAN OUT YOUR LOCKER?

03:54.024 --> 03:57.157
I HAD AN EVENT
TO GET TO.

03:57.157 --> 04:00.781
LOOK, I KNEW YOU WERE HAVING
A HARD TIME, BUT...

04:00.781 --> 04:02.823
I HAD NO IDEA
HOW BAD IT WAS.

04:02.823 --> 04:03.914
I'M SORRY.

04:03.914 --> 04:05.536
IT'S NOT YOUR FAULT.

04:05.536 --> 04:09.079
STILL, I'LL MISS
RIDING WITH YOU.

04:09.079 --> 04:11.131
I THINK WE MADE
A GOOD TEAM, THERE.

04:11.131 --> 04:14.425
IT'S NOTHING PERSONAL,
BEN.

04:14.425 --> 04:17.507
WILL I SEE YOU AROUND?

04:17.507 --> 04:19.139
YEAH.

04:19.139 --> 04:21.882
SEEMS LIKE WE HAVE
SOME OF THE SAME FRIENDS NOW.

04:21.882 --> 04:23.724
[ LOCKER SLAMS ]

04:26.887 --> 04:28.228
GUESS THAT'S IT.

04:28.228 --> 04:32.102
SO, WHAT'S JACK PORTER
DOING NEXT?

04:32.102 --> 04:37.027
SOMETHING I SHOULD'VE DONE
A LONG TIME AGO.

04:42.493 --> 04:44.575
James: EMILY WAS SEEN LEAVING
BEN HUNTER'S PLACE THIS MORNING.

04:44.575 --> 04:47.458
SEE WHAT YOU
CAN DIG UP ON HIM.

04:47.458 --> 04:50.331
WHY AM I STILL SPINNING
MY WHEELS ON THIS?

04:50.331 --> 04:52.252
I GAVE YOU VIDEO
OF JACK PORTER

04:52.252 --> 04:54.294
ADMITTING THAT HE KILLED
AN FBI AGENT.

04:54.294 --> 04:58.379
LEST YOU FORGET, THIS IS ABOUT
DESTROYING EMILY'S REPUTATION

04:58.379 --> 05:00.090
THE SAME WAY
SHE DID DANIEL'S.

05:00.090 --> 05:03.013
AND KNOW THIS --
NOTHING WILL GO TO WASTE.

05:03.013 --> 05:05.346
THAT VIDEO WILL BE
THE FIRST DOMINO

05:05.346 --> 05:07.428
IN EXPOSING
WHO SHE REALLY IS.

05:07.428 --> 05:08.689
SORRY TO INTERRUPT.

05:08.689 --> 05:10.100
HERE ARE THE QUARTERLY REPORTS
YOU ASKED FOR.

05:10.100 --> 05:12.102
MERCI, SIMONE.

05:14.435 --> 05:15.896
THANKS TO THE VIDEO,

05:15.896 --> 05:17.988
BY TOMORROW MORNING,
THE WORLD WILL HAVE

05:17.988 --> 05:21.402
A VERY DIFFERENT OPINION
OF EMILY THORNE.

05:22.903 --> 05:24.945
[ DOOR OPENS ]

05:30.831 --> 05:33.083
BUONGIORNO, MIO MARITO!

05:33.083 --> 05:34.084
[ GIGGLES ]

05:34.084 --> 05:35.506
ARE WE ITALIAN NOW?

05:35.506 --> 05:38.168
WELL, WE WILL BE IN ABOUT EIGHT
SHAKES OF A TURKEY LEG.

05:38.168 --> 05:39.720
MM, MORE OR LESS.

05:39.720 --> 05:42.553
BECAUSE WHAT IS
THE WEDDING OF THE CENTURY

05:42.553 --> 05:46.226
WITHOUT AN EQUALLY
EXTRAVAGANT HONEYMOON?

05:46.226 --> 05:47.267
[ CHUCKLES ]

05:47.267 --> 05:48.729
ITALY, HUH?

05:48.729 --> 05:49.810
MM, WHEREABOUT?

05:49.810 --> 05:51.021
WHEREVER THE ESPRESSO'S HOT

05:51.021 --> 05:52.272
AND THE MEN ARE HOTTER.

05:52.272 --> 05:55.235
WELL, I HEAR FLORENCE IS NICE
THIS TIME OF YEAR.

05:55.235 --> 05:56.647
GREAT!
SO PACK A BAG --

05:56.647 --> 05:58.399
OR JUST A CREDIT CARD.

05:58.399 --> 06:00.190
MY JET'S GETTING FUELED UP
AS WE SPEAK,

06:00.190 --> 06:01.982
SO WE'LL BE GOOD TO GO
WITHIN THE HOUR.

06:01.982 --> 06:03.113
[ CELLPHONE RINGING ]

06:03.113 --> 06:04.074
ARRIVEDERCI!

06:04.074 --> 06:06.246
[ CHUCKLES ]

06:06.246 --> 06:08.038
HELLO?

06:08.038 --> 06:10.080
YOU KNOW HOW YOU SAID
YOU'D PAY ME

06:10.080 --> 06:11.622
FOR ANY USEFUL INFORMATION?

06:13.624 --> 06:14.875
YEAH.

06:14.875 --> 06:16.166
MARGAUX HAS VIDEO FOOTAGE

06:16.166 --> 06:18.338
THAT SHE PLANS TO USE
AGAINST EMILY.

06:18.338 --> 06:19.630
FOOTAGE OF WHAT?

06:19.630 --> 06:21.672
I'm not sure, but she's
releasing it tomorrow.

06:21.672 --> 06:24.765
ALL RIGHT, SIMONE,
YOU HAVE TO GET THIS FOR ME.

06:24.765 --> 06:27.177
I'LL TRY, BUT MARGAUX'S BEING
VERY PROTECTIVE ABOUT IT.

06:27.177 --> 06:29.720
I CAN'T LOSE MY JOB
OVER THIS.

06:29.720 --> 06:31.101
WELL,
I'LL GET YOU A NEW ONE,

06:31.101 --> 06:33.604
EVEN IF THAT MEANS
I HAVE TO START A MAGAZINE.

06:33.604 --> 06:37.728
DO WHATEVER IT TAKES.

06:37.728 --> 06:43.694
Louise: IL TUO CULO SEMBRA BUONO
IN QUEI PANTALONES.

06:43.694 --> 06:46.156
THAT MEANS, "YOUR BUTT LOOKS
GOOD IN THOSE PANTS."

06:46.156 --> 06:48.238
[ CHUCKLES ]

06:48.238 --> 06:50.080
WHAT?

06:50.080 --> 06:52.082
[ SIGHS ]

06:52.082 --> 06:54.374
UM, SOMETHING CAME UP.

06:54.374 --> 06:55.666
I CAN'T LEAVE RIGHT NOW.

06:55.666 --> 06:58.378
WELL, HOW MUCH TIME DO YOU
NEED -- TWO, THREE HOURS?

06:58.378 --> 07:01.211
OH, PROBABLY
A LITTLE MORE THAN THAT.

07:01.211 --> 07:02.342
WHY DON'T YOU GO
WITHOUT ME?

07:02.342 --> 07:03.674
[ SLAPS LEGS ]

07:03.674 --> 07:05.135
IT'S OUR HONEYMOON!

07:05.135 --> 07:08.759
WELL...I'LL CATCH UP WITH YOU
IN A DAY OR SO,

07:08.759 --> 07:10.891
AND, UH, IN THE MEANTIME,

07:10.891 --> 07:14.895
YOU CAN TASTE-TEST YOUR WAY
TO THE BEST GELATERIA.

07:14.895 --> 07:16.106
[ CHUCKLES ]

07:16.106 --> 07:17.357
OF COURSE.

07:17.357 --> 07:20.981
[ Flatly ] GELATO.
YAY.

07:22.943 --> 07:25.946
Victoria: WHO THE HELL
ARE RALPH AND ALICE?

07:25.946 --> 07:27.778
EDWARD GRAYSON'S CORGIS.

07:27.778 --> 07:30.120
I'M SORRY.
WHAT IS THAT WORD?

07:30.120 --> 07:31.872
YOU'RE GETTING HIS DOGS.

07:31.872 --> 07:34.454
IT SAYS HERE
THEY'RE BEING FLOWN IN

07:34.454 --> 07:37.457
FROM SCOTTSDALE NEXT WEEK --
FIRST CLASS.

07:37.457 --> 07:39.960
THAT'S IT?

07:39.960 --> 07:41.211
[ SCOFFS ]

07:41.211 --> 07:44.004
THERE HAS TO BE
SOME MISTAKE.

07:44.004 --> 07:45.886
OH, WAIT, YOU'RE RIGHT.

07:45.886 --> 07:48.178
YOU'RE ALSO GETTING
THEIR BURBERRY DOG BEDS.

07:48.178 --> 07:50.390
I JUST NEED
YOUR SIGNATURE

07:50.390 --> 07:52.763
HERE, HERE,
AND INITIAL HERE.

07:52.763 --> 07:55.095
WHAT ABOUT
THE INHERITANCE?

07:55.095 --> 07:56.897
I'M SORRY, MRS. GRAYSON.

07:56.897 --> 07:59.059
THE REMAINDER OF
EDWARD GRAYSON'S ESTATE

07:59.059 --> 08:00.651
IS BEING LEFT TO HIS WIFE.

08:00.651 --> 08:02.102
HIS WIFE?

08:02.102 --> 08:04.484
[ SCOFFS ]
SHE DIED 20 YEARS AGO.

08:07.908 --> 08:09.530
SO SORRY I'M LATE.

08:25.085 --> 08:27.007
YOU'RE EDWARD'S WIFE?
THAT WAS YOUR SECRET?

08:27.007 --> 08:28.759
YOU'VE GOT TO ADMIT,
IT'S A GOOD ONE.

08:28.759 --> 08:30.591
WELL, THE LAST TIME
I SPOKE WITH HIM,

08:30.591 --> 08:33.724
HE WASN'T DATING,
NOR WAS HE REVISING HIS WILL.

08:33.724 --> 08:35.015
WHAT KIND OF SCAM IS THIS?

08:35.015 --> 08:36.395
THIS IS NO SCAM.

08:36.395 --> 08:38.097
TEDDY AND I WERE MARRIED
FOUR MONTHS AGO,

08:38.097 --> 08:41.311
SO YOUR CONVERSATION
WAS NOT A RECENT ONE.

08:41.311 --> 08:43.102
YOUR HUSBAND DIES
A WEEK AGO,

08:43.102 --> 08:44.144
AND THE FIRST THING
YOU DO

08:44.144 --> 08:45.485
IS HOP ON A PLANE
TO THE HAMPTONS,

08:45.485 --> 08:46.987
AND RATHER THAN TELLING ME

08:46.987 --> 08:48.949
THAT MY FATHER-IN-LAW
PASSED AWAY,

08:48.949 --> 08:51.451
YOU SPEND TWO DAYS CONCEALING
YOUR TRUE IDENTITY.

08:51.451 --> 08:52.492
AND FOR WHAT?

08:52.492 --> 08:54.114
TO GO PARTY-HOPPING,

08:54.114 --> 08:56.787
OR TO EMBARRASS ME
IN FRONT OF MY FRIENDS?

08:56.787 --> 08:58.158
I'LL GIVE YOU LADIES
SOME PRIVACY.

08:58.158 --> 09:01.662
OH, WE DON'T NEED PRIVACY.
WE NEED A JUDGE.

09:01.662 --> 09:03.754
THIS WILL IS FRAUDULENT.

09:09.169 --> 09:11.632
I CAME
TO THE HAMPTONS EARLY

09:11.632 --> 09:13.223
TO SEE WHAT KIND OF A PERSON
YOU ARE,

09:13.223 --> 09:15.225
TO MEET YOU IN A CIRCUMSTANCE

09:15.225 --> 09:18.058
WHERE YOU'RE NOT PREDISPOSED
TO HATE ME.

09:18.058 --> 09:20.681
AND MAYBE I WOULD'VE
SHOWN YOU SOME KINDNESS.

09:20.681 --> 09:24.444
BUT TO SEE YOU RAKE
YOUR FRIENDS OVER THE COALS?

09:24.444 --> 09:25.776
[ Laughing ]
OH.

09:25.776 --> 09:30.320
YOU ARE JUST AS VICIOUS
AS TEDDY MADE YOU OUT TO BE.

09:30.320 --> 09:32.743
EDWARD ADORED ME.

09:32.743 --> 09:35.495
AND HE ALWAYS PROMISED
TO LOOK AFTER MY FAMILY.

09:35.495 --> 09:36.827
AS A MATTER OF FACT,

09:36.827 --> 09:38.829
HE REVIEWED
HIS WILL WITH ME,

09:38.829 --> 09:41.411
AND I KNOW FULL WELL
WHAT WAS COMING TO ME

09:41.411 --> 09:43.333
AND TO MY SON, DANIEL.

09:43.333 --> 09:44.755
WELL, ALL I KNOW

09:44.755 --> 09:47.007
IS THAT SHORTLY AFTER
CONRAD'S ARREST,

09:47.007 --> 09:49.089
TEDDY'S ILLNESS TOOK A TURN,

09:49.089 --> 09:51.211
AND WHEN HE TRIED
TO REACH OUT TO YOU,

09:51.211 --> 09:52.592
YOU WERE NOWHERE
TO BE FOUND.

09:52.592 --> 09:55.215
SO WHEN THE GOING GOT TOUGH,
YOU JUMPED SHIP.

09:55.215 --> 09:57.177
I DID NO SUCH THING.

09:57.177 --> 09:58.639
[ SCREAMS ]

09:58.639 --> 10:00.641
BUT YOU KNOW
WHAT WAS CURIOUS?

10:00.641 --> 10:02.222
AFTER MY SON PASSED AWAY,

10:02.222 --> 10:04.855
I LEFT MULTIPLE MESSAGES
FOR EDWARD.

10:04.855 --> 10:08.358
NOW, ARE YOU THE REASON WHY
HE NEVER CALLED ME BACK?

10:08.358 --> 10:11.361
I THOUGHT IT BEST
TO KEEP HIS SPIRITS UP,

10:11.361 --> 10:13.734
BECAUSE YOU HAD DONE
ENOUGH DAMAGE.

10:13.734 --> 10:15.575
WHAT YOU DID TO HIS HEART --

10:15.575 --> 10:17.617
NOT EVEN THIS NURSE
COULD HELP.

10:17.617 --> 10:19.199
YOU WERE HIS NURSE?

10:19.199 --> 10:22.913
OH, WELL, THIS COULDN'T
BE MORE TRANSPARENT.

10:22.913 --> 10:25.165
YOU TOOK ADVANTAGE
OF AN AILING MAN

10:25.165 --> 10:27.127
WHO WAS CLEARLY
WASN'T IN HIS RIGHT MIND.

10:27.127 --> 10:28.588
ANY JUDGE WILL SEE THAT.

10:28.588 --> 10:32.212
TEDDY WAS CLEAR-MINDED
TO THE END,

10:32.212 --> 10:35.015
AND HE THOUGHT
THE VERY WORST OF YOU,

10:35.015 --> 10:38.759
WHICH IS WHY HE LEFT YOU
TWO INCONTINENT DOGS

10:38.759 --> 10:42.813
AND ME EVERYTHING ELSE.

10:45.816 --> 10:47.107
Jack:
 NOT LOSING ANY SLEEP

10:47.107 --> 10:49.359
OVER WHAT THE REST OF THE WORLD
THINKS ABOUT ME.

10:49.359 --> 10:52.032
I KILLED AN FBI AGENT.

10:52.032 --> 10:53.613
IS THERE MORE?

10:53.613 --> 10:56.196
THAT WAS ALL
SIMONE COULD RETRIEVE

10:56.196 --> 10:57.197
BEFORE ALMOST
GETTING CAUGHT.

10:57.197 --> 10:58.989
NOW SHE'S WORRIED
MARGAUX'S ON TO HER, SO...

10:58.989 --> 11:01.121
IT'S UP TO US.

11:01.121 --> 11:04.544
I SHOULD'VE KNOWN MARGAUX
WAS TOO SMART TO PLAY DUMB.

11:04.544 --> 11:06.416
GOD, IF THIS GETS OUT...

11:06.416 --> 11:08.418
IT'S GONNA DESTROY JACK.

11:08.418 --> 11:09.840
HOW MUCH TIME
DO WE HAVE?

11:09.840 --> 11:11.291
SHE'S RELEASING IT
TOMORROW.

11:11.291 --> 11:13.754
WELL, THEN,
WE'D BETTER GET HACKING.

11:13.754 --> 11:16.346
IF YOUR COMPUTER SYSTEM'S
BEEN COMPROMISED,

11:16.346 --> 11:18.138
IT'S LIKELY TO BE
A CYBER ATTACK.

11:18.138 --> 11:19.349
WE'LL SEND OVER
A TASK FORCE.

11:19.349 --> 11:21.061
THE COMPUTER IN QUESTION
IS AIR-GAPPED,

11:21.061 --> 11:23.393
WHICH MEANS IT'S UNTOUCHED
BY THE INTERNET

11:23.393 --> 11:25.515
AND THEREFORE UNHACKABLE.

11:25.515 --> 11:27.227
SOMEONE BROKE IN
TO THE SERVER ROOM

11:27.227 --> 11:30.480
TO GET AT IT AT 10:37.

11:30.480 --> 11:32.112
YOU KNOW
THE EXACT MOMENT?

11:32.112 --> 11:33.443
I RECEIVE AN ALERT

11:33.443 --> 11:35.906
ANYTIME THE COMPUTER
IS TURNED ON.

11:35.906 --> 11:38.618
BY THE TIME I GOT TO IT,
THE SERVER ROOM WAS EMPTY.

11:38.618 --> 11:40.160
DO YOU HAVE ANY IDEA
WHAT THEY WERE AFTER?

11:40.160 --> 11:41.241
NOT SURE.

11:41.241 --> 11:42.492
IT'S POSSIBLE I ARRIVED

11:42.492 --> 11:44.204
BEFORE THEY COULD FINISH
THE JOB.

11:44.204 --> 11:45.996
WELL, WE HAVE
YOUR VISITORS' LOG

11:45.996 --> 11:47.037
AND YOUR SECURITY FOOTAGE,

11:47.037 --> 11:48.288
SO WE'LL START THERE.

11:48.288 --> 11:49.499
IN THE MEANTIME,
DO YOU KNOW ANYONE

11:49.499 --> 11:51.041
WHO COULD BE
TARGETING YOU?

11:51.041 --> 11:52.923
I AM THE CEO

11:52.923 --> 11:55.756
OF AN INTERNATIONAL MEDIA
CONGLOMERATE, AGENT LIN.

11:55.756 --> 11:56.757
THAT MAKES ME --

11:56.757 --> 11:57.928
EVERYBODY'S TARGET.

11:57.928 --> 12:00.390
BUT A MIDDAY BREAK-IN?

12:00.390 --> 12:02.052
GOOD MONEY'S
ON AN INSIDE JOB.

12:19.619 --> 12:22.913
[ LAUGHTER ]

12:22.913 --> 12:23.994
FIND THE SEA GLASS!

12:23.994 --> 12:26.206
[ LAUGHTER ]

12:26.206 --> 12:27.247
[ PUPPY YIPS ]

12:27.247 --> 12:28.288
David: HEY, JACK!

12:35.005 --> 12:36.046
NICE SUIT.

12:36.046 --> 12:37.087
WHAT'S THE OCCASION?

12:37.087 --> 12:40.300
AH, IT'S JUST...
OLD FRIEND OF MINE --

12:40.300 --> 12:42.052
HE WANTS ME
TO JOIN HIS FIRM.

12:42.052 --> 12:44.644
I'M SUPPOSED TO MEET HIM
AND TALK ABOUT IT.

12:44.644 --> 12:45.846
NICE.

12:45.846 --> 12:47.557
THAT SOUNDS LIKE
A GOOD OPPORTUNITY.

12:47.557 --> 12:49.729
[ CHUCKLES ]
I DON'T THINK I'M GONNA GO.

12:49.729 --> 12:52.232
STEPPING BACK INTO THAT WORLD,
I JUST, UH, I DON'T FEEL

12:52.232 --> 12:54.564
LIKE IT'S WHAT
I'M SUPPOSED TO DO.

12:54.564 --> 12:56.486
NOT THAT I KNOW
WHAT I SHOULD BE DOING.

12:58.278 --> 12:59.399
YOU'RE REBUILDING
A RELATIONSHIP

12:59.399 --> 13:01.111
WITH YOUR DAUGHTER.

13:01.111 --> 13:02.032
THAT'S NO SMALL THING.

13:02.032 --> 13:03.703
YEAH, IT DOESN'T
REALLY FEEL

13:03.703 --> 13:05.495
LIKE A FULL-TIME JOB.

13:05.495 --> 13:09.039
LOOK, NO ONE KNOWS
WHAT THE FUTURE HOLDS,

13:09.039 --> 13:10.210
BUT IF YOU'RE AN OPTIMIST,

13:10.210 --> 13:13.333
THAT...JUST MEANS
ANYTHING IS POSSIBLE.

13:16.546 --> 13:19.549
LAST TIME THAT I KNEW WHAT
I SHOULD BE DOING WITH MY LIFE

13:19.549 --> 13:21.471
WAS THE SUMMER THAT I
BOUGHT THE BEACH HOUSE --

13:21.471 --> 13:24.094
JUST FIXING IT UP
A LITTLE BIT AT A TIME.

13:24.094 --> 13:26.136
YEAH.

13:26.136 --> 13:27.807
I KNOW WHAT YOU MEAN,
YEAH.

13:27.807 --> 13:29.189
F-FOR ME IT WAS THE,
UH...

13:29.189 --> 13:31.271
IT WAS THE BOAT.

13:31.271 --> 13:33.894
I WAS GONNA SAIL TO HAITI.

13:33.894 --> 13:35.936
THAT WAS...THREE YEARS AGO.

13:35.936 --> 13:37.607
WHAT STOPPED YOU?

13:39.900 --> 13:41.902
MY DAD DIED.

13:41.902 --> 13:44.034
AND THEN I, UH,

13:44.034 --> 13:46.706
I HAD TO STICK AROUND AND TAKE
CARE OF MY LITTLE BROTHER.

13:48.328 --> 13:50.790
AND YOUR DAUGHTER SHOWED UP.

13:57.007 --> 13:58.088
YOU TWO USED TO LOVE

13:58.088 --> 14:00.050
SCOURING THE BEACH
FOR SEA GLASS.

14:00.050 --> 14:02.722
YEAH.

14:02.722 --> 14:04.054
WE WOULD LAY THEM ALL OUT

14:04.054 --> 14:06.386
AND SEE WHICH ONES
WERE WORTH KEEPING.

14:06.386 --> 14:07.847
[ CHUCKLES ]

14:07.847 --> 14:10.891
YOU GUYS --
YOU WERE INSEPARABLE.

14:10.891 --> 14:13.563
THAT NEVER REALLY CHANGED,
DID IT?

14:13.563 --> 14:15.235
THAT LOOKS LIKE
A PRETTY GOOD ONE.

14:17.357 --> 14:18.738
YEAH.

14:21.031 --> 14:24.074
YEAH, IT SURE DOES.

14:36.256 --> 14:39.169
COME IN.

14:39.169 --> 14:41.381
EMILY?

14:41.381 --> 14:43.593
JACK, HI.

14:45.505 --> 14:46.967
WE NEED TO TALK.

14:46.967 --> 14:48.388
I KNOW.

14:50.510 --> 14:51.891
WAIT, YOU -- YOU DO?

14:51.891 --> 14:53.103
AND I DON'T KNOW THE EXTENT

14:53.103 --> 14:54.224
OF THE FOOTAGE
THAT MARGAUX HAS,

14:54.224 --> 14:56.106
BUT WE WILL FIGURE IT OUT.

14:56.106 --> 14:57.978
WHAT ARE YOU
TALKING ABOUT?

14:57.978 --> 15:00.190
NOLAN DIDN'T CALL YOU?

15:00.190 --> 15:02.442
[ SIGHS ]

15:02.442 --> 15:03.443
I WAS ABOUT TO.

15:05.325 --> 15:06.786
NOW YOU GET TO TELL HIM.
 TELL ME WHAT?

15:06.786 --> 15:08.578
WHAT -- WHAT'S GOING ON?

15:08.578 --> 15:11.161
MARGAUX HAS A VIDEO OF US
TALKING ABOUT KATE.

15:11.161 --> 15:12.993
YOU ADMIT TO KILLING HER,

15:12.993 --> 15:14.995
AND WE BOTH
COP TO COVERING IT UP.

15:14.995 --> 15:16.536
AND SO, WHAT,
SHE'S GONNA RELEASE IT?

15:16.536 --> 15:17.998
SHE'S GONNA TRY.

15:17.998 --> 15:19.539
HAVE YOU SEEN THE VIDEO?

15:19.539 --> 15:21.171
JUST A CLIP OF IT.
I'LL PULL IT UP.

15:22.672 --> 15:23.803
[ KEYS CLACKING ]

15:35.645 --> 15:37.107
I KILLED AN FBI AGENT --
A BAD ONE...

15:37.107 --> 15:38.018
DAMN IT!
[ CLAPS HANDS ]

15:38.018 --> 15:39.229
IF THIS THING GETS RELEASED,
MY LIFE IS OVER.

15:39.229 --> 15:40.270
ARE YOU SURE YOU CAN'T GET

15:40.270 --> 15:41.611
INTO LeMARCHAL'S COMPUTER
SYSTEM?

15:41.611 --> 15:43.483
THIS SPECIFIC COMPUTER
IS UNHACKABLE,

15:43.483 --> 15:46.736
BUT MARGAUX'S SECURITY SYSTEM
IS NOT.

15:46.736 --> 15:47.988
WAIT, YOU GUYS
ARE BREAKING IN?

15:47.988 --> 15:49.119
Emily: TONIGHT.

15:49.119 --> 15:51.371
THE ONLY WAY TO GET THE FILE
IS TO STEAL THE COMPUTER.

15:51.371 --> 15:53.163
NO, IT'S NOT.

15:53.163 --> 15:54.374
LAST NIGHT,
MARGAUX AND I HAD

15:54.374 --> 15:56.166
OUR FIRST REAL CONVERSATION
SINCE WE SPLIT.

15:56.166 --> 15:57.537
IT WAS ALMOST
LIKE WE WERE FRIENDS.

15:57.537 --> 15:58.578
I WILL TALK TO HER.

15:58.578 --> 15:59.959
NO, YOU COULD MAKE
THINGS WORSE.

15:59.959 --> 16:01.081
I DON'T WANT HER TIPPED OFF.

16:01.081 --> 16:02.882
AND I DON'T WANT THE TRUTH
COMING OUT.

16:02.882 --> 16:05.045
IT'S MY ASS ON THE LINE.
I KILLED AN FBI AGENT -- ME!

16:05.045 --> 16:07.087
I CAN'T LEAVE ANYTHING
TO CHANCE.

16:07.087 --> 16:09.139
NOW, IF THAT MEANS CONFRONTING
MARGAUX HEAD-ON, SO BE IT.

16:09.139 --> 16:10.090
ALL RIGHT,
YOU HAVE TO TRUST ME.

16:10.090 --> 16:14.014
NOT THIS TIME.

16:14.014 --> 16:15.145
[ SIGHS ]

16:15.145 --> 16:17.017
I'LL TALK TO HIM.

16:17.017 --> 16:18.148
YEAH, YOU'D BETTER,

16:18.148 --> 16:20.020
BECAUSE MARGAUX
CANNOT KNOW WE'RE COMING.

16:21.731 --> 16:24.104
[ MID-TEMPO MUSIC PLAYING ]

16:26.236 --> 16:29.199
Lyman: AND HOW IS MY FAVORITE
UNREAL HOUSEWIFE?

16:32.072 --> 16:34.114
WELL, I WAS HOPING
YOU WOULD HAVE CAUGHT

16:34.114 --> 16:36.456
A RIDE OUT OF TOWN
ON MAMA'S BROOM.

16:36.456 --> 16:38.748
AND MISS THE MOMENT
YOU COME TO YOUR SENSES?

16:38.748 --> 16:40.830
AND WHICH SENSES
WOULD THOSE BE,

16:40.830 --> 16:43.002
THE ONES WHERE I DECIDE
TO FINANCE

16:43.002 --> 16:44.714
YOUR ANEMIC
POLITICAL CAMPAIGN?

16:44.714 --> 16:46.886
Woman: ANYTHING FOR YOUR FRIEND,
MRS. ROSS?

16:46.886 --> 16:49.049
OH, NO, DEAR,
HE WON'T BE STAYING.

16:50.550 --> 16:52.552
"MRS. ROSS"?

16:54.554 --> 16:56.096
NOW, COME ON.
YOU WON.

16:56.096 --> 16:57.437
YOU GOT YOUR MONEY.

16:57.437 --> 17:00.690
MUST YOU SIT HERE AND MAKE
A MOCKERY OUT OF MARRIAGE?

17:00.690 --> 17:04.404
LOOK, NOLAN AND I HAVE MORE
AFFECTION FOR EACH OTHER

17:04.404 --> 17:05.565
THAN MOST COUPLES I KNOW.

17:05.565 --> 17:08.407
WELL, THEN, PRAY TELL --
WHERE IS HE?

17:08.407 --> 17:09.739
HE HAD SOME WORK TO DO.

17:09.739 --> 17:11.361
THE MAN DOES NOT HAVE A JOB,

17:11.361 --> 17:14.324
EXCEPT FOR MAKING SURE THIS
PLACE KEEPS YOU WELL-HYDRATED.

17:14.324 --> 17:16.076
DAY AFTER YOUR RECEPTION,
HERE YOU SIT ALONE.

17:16.076 --> 17:18.208
YOUR MARRIAGE IS A SHAM.
EVERYBODY KNOWS IT.

17:18.208 --> 17:21.040
WELL, AT LEAST I'M CREATING
A LIFE FOR MYSELF,

17:21.040 --> 17:24.794
WHICH IS A WHOLE LOT MORE
THAN I CAN SAY FOR YOU.

17:24.794 --> 17:27.217
YOUR CAMPAIGN IS SINKING,

17:27.217 --> 17:31.341
AND, WELL [SIGHS] GOLLY,
THAT IS JUST ALL YOU HAVE.

17:34.013 --> 17:35.135
SILLY GIRL.

17:35.135 --> 17:37.887
YOU SHOULD KNOW BETTER
THAN TO DOUBT ME.

17:37.887 --> 17:41.141
I ALWAYS FIND A WAY
TO COME OUT ON TOP.

17:47.187 --> 17:49.649
WHAT ABOUT
STICKLEY FURNITURE?

17:49.649 --> 17:51.781
DO YOU KNOW OF ANY
LOCAL COLLECTORS?

17:51.781 --> 17:53.283
YOU LOST ME
AT "STICKLEY."

17:53.283 --> 17:55.115
SO THAT WOULD BE A "NO."

17:56.616 --> 17:58.998
THERE'S AN ANTIQUE
DEALER...

17:58.998 --> 18:01.040
A FEW MILES DOWN THE ROAD.

18:01.040 --> 18:03.413
YOU'RE DAVID CLARKE.

18:03.413 --> 18:05.125
YEAH, I AM.

18:06.966 --> 18:08.007
NATALIE WATERS.

18:08.007 --> 18:09.299
AH.

18:09.299 --> 18:10.880
A PERSON WHO OBVIOUSLY
WATCHES THE NEWS.

18:10.880 --> 18:15.215
AH.
NICE TO MEET YOU.

18:15.215 --> 18:18.308
YOU, UH, IN THE MARKET
FOR MISSION FURNITURE?

18:18.308 --> 18:21.811
ACTUALLY, UH, I'M JUST
TRYING TO FIND A GOOD HOME

18:21.811 --> 18:23.102
FOR A COUPLE OF CHAIRS...

18:23.102 --> 18:25.275
AND A SET OF ANTIQUE SPOONS,

18:25.275 --> 18:28.148
AND MORE GOLF CLUBS THAN
YOU CAN POSSIBLY IMAGINE,

18:28.148 --> 18:30.190
AMONG OTHER THINGS.

18:30.190 --> 18:32.492
I RECENTLY LOST SOMEONE,

18:32.492 --> 18:36.156
AND THIS IS MY INHERITANCE.

18:36.156 --> 18:38.117
I'M SORRY FOR YOUR LOSS.

18:38.117 --> 18:39.539
THANK YOU.

18:39.539 --> 18:42.001
IT'S, UM...
IT'S BEEN OVERWHELMING.

18:42.001 --> 18:44.244
I'M JUST TRYING
TO PLACE THESE ITEMS

18:44.244 --> 18:46.085
WITH PEOPLE
WHO WILL APPRECIATE THEM

18:46.085 --> 18:47.297
AS MUCH AS HE DID.

18:47.297 --> 18:52.172
SO, UH [CHUCKLES]
IF YOU KNOW ANYONE

18:52.172 --> 18:55.715
WHO HAS A THING FOR, UH...

18:55.715 --> 18:57.637
RUSSIAN NESTING DOLLS...

18:57.637 --> 18:59.018
[ CHUCKLES ]
 OH, WOW, YEAH.

18:59.018 --> 19:00.019
DOESN'T EVERYONE?

19:01.931 --> 19:03.723
WHAT'S YOUR PLAN
FOR THAT KETCH?

19:03.723 --> 19:04.814
THE BOAT?

19:04.814 --> 19:08.067
MM-HMM.

19:08.067 --> 19:10.190
TO GIVE IT TO THE NICE MAN
I MET AT THE BAR...

19:10.190 --> 19:12.402
IF HE PROMISES
TO TAKE CARE OF IT.

19:12.402 --> 19:13.943
[ CHUCKLES ]

19:13.943 --> 19:15.074
WELL, YOU SHOULDN'T
GIVE IT AWAY.

19:15.074 --> 19:17.277
YOU SHOULD ASK THE NICE MAN

19:17.277 --> 19:18.908
FOR FAIR MARKET VALUE.

19:18.908 --> 19:21.040
OKAY.

19:23.162 --> 19:26.586
HOW ABOUT YOU BUY ME
A DRINK...AND IT'S YOURS?

19:26.586 --> 19:28.167
[ CHUCKLES ]

19:28.167 --> 19:30.920
♪ EVERY NIGHT AND DAY ♪

19:30.920 --> 19:32.171
Victoria:
I DON'T UNDERSTAND.

19:32.171 --> 19:34.344
WILLS ARE CONTESTED
ALL THE TIME.

19:34.344 --> 19:36.216
Susan: OKAY.

19:36.216 --> 19:37.096
I COULD TAKE THIS ON

19:37.096 --> 19:39.098
AND CHALK UP A BUNCH
OF BILLABLE HOURS,

19:39.098 --> 19:41.261
BUT BASED ON YOUR CURRENT
FINANCIAL SITUATION --

19:41.261 --> 19:42.722
THAT WOMAN
IS A CRIMINAL.

19:42.722 --> 19:46.396
SHE DUPED A DYING MAN OUT OF
MILLIONS -- MY MILLIONS.

19:46.396 --> 19:48.147
I'M SORRY, VICTORIA.

19:48.147 --> 19:51.070
I'M NOT SURE IF YOU CAN
EVEN AFFORD THIS HOUR.

19:57.367 --> 19:59.449
Lyman:
MY APOLOGIES.

19:59.449 --> 20:01.080
I COULDN'T HELP
BUT OVERHEAR.

20:01.080 --> 20:03.082
NO ONE EVER MEANS THAT.

20:03.082 --> 20:04.784
LYMAN ELLIS --

20:04.784 --> 20:07.377
FUTURE CONGRESSMAN,
CURRENT LAWYER,

20:07.377 --> 20:09.208
AND THE MAN
WHO WILL TAKE ON YOUR CASE.

20:09.208 --> 20:10.750
[ CHUCKLES ]
DO I KNOW YOU?

20:10.750 --> 20:12.752
YOU KNOW MY SISTER, LOUISE.

20:12.752 --> 20:16.426
NOW, I SAW YOU,
AT HER RECEPTION,

20:16.426 --> 20:17.887
RAISE MORE MONEY
IN ONE HOUR

20:17.887 --> 20:19.178
THAN I'VE SEEN
AT ANY POLITICAL FUNDRAISER.

20:19.178 --> 20:21.100
YOU'RE SCRAPPY.
[ LAUGHS ]

20:21.100 --> 20:23.052
I'M SORRY, MR. ELLIS,

20:23.052 --> 20:24.804
BUT THE ANSWER IS NO.

20:24.804 --> 20:26.766
AND I HAVEN'T EVEN ASKED YOU
A QUESTION YET.

20:26.766 --> 20:29.188
LIKE I SAID, SCRAPPY.

20:29.188 --> 20:31.190
NOW, WHAT WOULD YOU SAY
IF I TOLD YOU

20:31.190 --> 20:32.562
I COULD GET YOU YOUR MONEY --

20:32.562 --> 20:34.063
ALL OF IT?

20:34.063 --> 20:36.115
I WOULD INSIST
THAT YOU FIRST TELL ME

20:36.115 --> 20:37.447
WHY I SHOULD
BELIEVE YOU.

20:37.447 --> 20:39.028
WELL, I UNDERSTAND
HOW IT FEELS

20:39.028 --> 20:40.490
TO BE SCREWED
OUT OF AN INHERITANCE.

20:40.490 --> 20:42.241
AND LIKE YOU,

20:42.241 --> 20:46.165
I'M WILLING
TO DO WHATEVER IT TAKES.

20:46.165 --> 20:48.037
SO WOULDN'T IT BE PRUDENT
FOR US TO POOL OUR ENERGIES

20:48.037 --> 20:50.540
TO MAKE SURE YOU GET BACK
WHAT IS RIGHTFULLY YOURS?

20:50.540 --> 20:54.083
I NEED A LAWYER,
NOT AN OPPORTUNIST.

20:54.083 --> 20:56.135
WELL, IT'S A GOOD THING
FOR YOU THAT I'M BOTH.

20:56.135 --> 20:57.136
WELL, WHAT'S IN IT FOR YOU?

20:57.136 --> 21:00.470
20% -- BASED ON WHAT
I ACCIDENTALLY OVERHEARD,

21:00.470 --> 21:01.641
THAT SHOULD BE
MORE THAN ENOUGH

21:01.641 --> 21:03.142
TO FUND MY CAMPAIGN
THROUGH ELECTION DAY.

21:03.142 --> 21:06.346
[ CHUCKLES ]

21:06.346 --> 21:08.808
MRS. GRAYSON, IF I LOSE,

21:08.808 --> 21:11.771
20% OF NOTHING IS NOTHING.

21:11.771 --> 21:13.813
YOU COULD NOT ASK
FOR A BETTER PROPOSITION.

21:13.813 --> 21:16.195
PROVE TO ME YOUR WORTH.

21:16.195 --> 21:19.108
IF YOU FIND
SOMETHING USEFUL,

21:19.108 --> 21:21.110
I'LL CONSIDER IT.

21:25.034 --> 21:29.499
THANKS FOR MEETING ME.

21:29.499 --> 21:30.870
WE NEED TO TALK.

21:40.510 --> 21:42.592
I CAN'T BELIEVE
HOW BIG CARL IS.

21:42.592 --> 21:43.763
[ CHUCKLES ]

21:43.763 --> 21:45.134
I'M GLAD YOU
BROUGHT HIM ALONG.

21:45.134 --> 21:47.016
WELL, I DIDN'T HAVE
MUCH OF A CHOICE.

21:47.016 --> 21:48.848
DAYCARE CLOSED EARLY,

21:48.848 --> 21:51.561
SO DADDY DAY
IN THE PARK.

21:51.561 --> 21:53.813
WHAT DID YOU WANT
TO TALK ABOUT?

21:55.815 --> 21:58.147
WELL, IT'S GONNA...
SOUND STUPID,

21:58.147 --> 22:01.150
BUT, UH, AFTER WE TALKED
YESTERDAY, I --

22:01.150 --> 22:02.942
I COULDN'T STOP THINKING
ABOUT HOW WE BROKE UP

22:02.942 --> 22:06.035
AND HOW I SAID SOME THINGS
THAT WEREN'T FAIR,

22:06.035 --> 22:08.247
AND...I JUST --

22:08.247 --> 22:12.161
I THOUGHT
THAT I SHOULD CALL.

22:12.161 --> 22:16.085
TO BE HONEST, I DID SOME
THINGS THAT WEREN'T FAIR.

22:17.837 --> 22:20.089
WELL, I JUST WANT YOU
TO KNOW

22:20.089 --> 22:21.461
THAT GOING FORWARD...

22:21.461 --> 22:24.424
I'M HERE FOR YOU,

22:24.424 --> 22:27.266
SINGLE PARENT
TO SINGLE PARENT.

22:27.266 --> 22:30.019
I APPRECIATE THAT.

22:30.019 --> 22:32.271
I CAN'T QUITE FATHOM

22:32.271 --> 22:34.684
HOW MUCH MY LIFE
WILL CHANGE --

22:34.684 --> 22:36.355
NOT JUST EMOTIONALLY,
BUT PRACTICALLY.

22:36.355 --> 22:39.108
WHEN WAS THE LAST TIME

22:39.108 --> 22:41.320
YOU WERE ABLE TO DO
SOMETHING SPONTANEOUS?

22:41.320 --> 22:43.903
UH...

22:43.903 --> 22:44.904
[ CHUCKLES ]

22:44.904 --> 22:45.945
OKAY.

22:45.945 --> 22:46.986
[ Laughing ] I, UM --
THE OTHER NIGHT,

22:46.986 --> 22:49.158
I GOT OUT OF BED
AND MADE MYSELF

22:49.158 --> 22:50.329
A GRILLED CHEESE SANDWICH.

22:50.329 --> 22:51.621
NO PLANNING.
I JUST DID IT.

22:51.621 --> 22:52.872
OH, SO YOU'RE SAYING

22:52.872 --> 22:55.705
I SHOULD SAVOR THE THEATER
THIS EVENING?

22:55.705 --> 22:57.707
WELL, I'D NEVER TELL YOU
WHAT TO DO,

22:57.707 --> 22:59.419
BUT I WILL SAY...

22:59.419 --> 23:01.170
WHAT IS THE THEATER AGAIN?

23:01.170 --> 23:04.003
[ LAUGHS ]
WOW, SOME PEP TALK.

23:04.003 --> 23:05.094
LOOK, IT'S JUST THAT,
YOU KNOW,

23:05.094 --> 23:06.716
Y-YOUR PRIORITIES CHANGE.

23:06.716 --> 23:08.177
YOU GET A NEW PERSPECTIVE.

23:08.177 --> 23:11.771
YOU KNOW, NOW EVERY DECISION
THAT I MAKE,

23:11.771 --> 23:14.974
I THINK, "HOW IS THIS GONNA
AFFECT CARL?" YOU KNOW.

23:14.974 --> 23:17.607
WHAT -- WHAT KIND OF EXAMPLE
AM I SETTING?

23:17.607 --> 23:21.861
YEAH, IT IS A LOT
TO CONSIDER.

23:21.861 --> 23:23.443
HEY, BUDDY!

23:23.443 --> 23:24.694
HEY!

23:24.694 --> 23:26.405
[ LAUGHS ]
NO, GIVE IT TO HER. NICE!

23:26.405 --> 23:27.447
YOU'RE GIVING THAT TO ME?

23:27.447 --> 23:28.948
THANK YOU.

23:28.948 --> 23:31.200
IT'S A LIMITED EDITION.

23:31.200 --> 23:32.241
[ LAUGHS ]

23:32.241 --> 23:33.793
YOU DON'T ACTUALLY
HAVE TO WEAR IT.

23:33.793 --> 23:37.036
THE THINGS A PARENT DOES
FOR THEIR CHILD.

23:38.588 --> 23:40.750
YOU'LL KNOW
SOON ENOUGH.

23:43.803 --> 23:45.094
[ CHUCKLES ]

23:46.345 --> 23:49.308
READY TO PROVE YOUR WORTH?

23:49.308 --> 23:51.390
NATALIE WATERS
BEGAN WORKING

23:51.390 --> 23:53.513
FOR EDWARD GRAYSON
SIX MONTHS AGO

23:53.513 --> 23:55.184
AS HIS PRIVATE NURSE,

23:55.184 --> 23:56.055
WHILE SHE
WAS STILL MARRIED.

23:56.055 --> 23:57.607
A FEW WEEKS IN,
SHE GOT A QUICKIE DIVORCE,

23:57.607 --> 24:00.149
FOLLOWED BY AN EVEN QUICKER
MARRIAGE TO MR. GRAYSON.

24:00.149 --> 24:01.060
AND...?

24:01.060 --> 24:02.942
THAT'S A MATTER
OF PUBLIC RECORD.

24:02.942 --> 24:04.193
WHERE'S THE DIRT?

24:04.193 --> 24:07.867
IT SEEMS THAT NURSE WATERS
IS ANYTHING BUT.

24:07.867 --> 24:09.198
SHE HAD HER CREDENTIALS
STRIPPED

24:09.198 --> 24:10.910
AFTER SHE WAS FIRED
FROM A HOSPITAL

24:10.910 --> 24:12.451
FOR SWINDLING A PATIENT
OUT OF MONEY.

24:12.451 --> 24:15.124
SO THAT GOES TO
A PATTERN OF BEHAVIOR,

24:15.124 --> 24:16.205
WHICH IS WHY
I HAVE ALREADY

24:16.205 --> 24:17.707
FILED THE PAPERWORK
TO CONTEST THE WILL.

24:17.707 --> 24:20.169
WELL, THAT SOUNDS
MORE LIKE A LAWYER TALKING.

24:20.169 --> 24:21.921
A LAWYER?

24:21.921 --> 24:24.293
MY LAWYER.

24:24.293 --> 24:27.967
[ KEYS CLACKING ]

24:29.008 --> 24:30.179
[ GASPS ]

24:30.179 --> 24:31.721
[ LAUGHS ]

24:31.721 --> 24:34.854
HEY, I THOUGHT YOU'D BE
HALFWAY TO ITALY BY NOW.

24:34.854 --> 24:37.517
MM, I'VE SEEN ITALY.

24:37.517 --> 24:39.398
I WANTED TO SEE IT
WITH YOU.

24:39.398 --> 24:42.021
OH.

24:42.021 --> 24:43.983
I'M SORRY.

24:43.983 --> 24:45.104
IT'S JUST --

24:45.104 --> 24:47.236
YEAH, SOMETHING CAME UP.
I KNOW.

24:49.779 --> 24:51.320
LOOK [SIGHS]

24:51.320 --> 24:54.574
I REALIZE YOU DID ME
THIS HUGE FAVOR,

24:54.574 --> 24:57.036
FOR WHICH I'M ETERNALLY
GRATEFUL,

24:57.036 --> 24:58.377
BUT I WOULDN'T
HAVE MARRIED YOU

24:58.377 --> 24:59.669
IF I DIDN'T LIKE YOU.

24:59.669 --> 25:02.211
AND, YES, I GOT CONTROL
OF MY MONEY, BUT...

25:02.211 --> 25:05.464
I ALSO GOT A FRIEND
IN THE PROCESS.

25:05.464 --> 25:08.678
WHAT ARE YOU SAYING?

25:08.678 --> 25:10.179
I'LL HAVE MY LAWYER

25:10.179 --> 25:13.302
DRAFT DIVORCE PAPERS
AND SET YOU FREE.

25:13.302 --> 25:17.436
OH, LOUISE.

25:17.436 --> 25:20.730
IT'S -- IT'S NOT THAT
AT ALL.

25:20.730 --> 25:23.903
I-I LOVE SPENDING TIME
WITH YOU,

25:23.903 --> 25:26.105
AND ITALY SOUNDS PERFECT.

25:26.105 --> 25:27.196
BUT...

25:27.196 --> 25:29.569
THERE'S THAT "BUT" AGAIN --

25:29.569 --> 25:31.701
AND NOT THE "LOOKS GOOD
IN THOSE PANTS" KIND.

25:31.701 --> 25:33.743
[ SIGHS ]

25:33.743 --> 25:35.114
OKAY, TODAY...

25:35.114 --> 25:37.326
SOMETHING IMPORTANT
CAME UP.

25:37.326 --> 25:39.038
AND THE THING IS...

25:43.462 --> 25:44.584
...EMILY AND I --

25:44.584 --> 25:46.796
[ GASPS ]

25:46.796 --> 25:49.508
YOU'RE SLEEPING TOGETHER?
[ GASPS ]

25:49.508 --> 25:50.590
NO, NO, NO.

25:50.590 --> 25:52.722
NO.
UM...EMILY AND I...

25:52.722 --> 25:56.015
OH, GOD.
HOW DO I EXPLAIN THIS?

25:58.768 --> 26:01.060
WE'RE SORT OF
LIKE SUPERHEROES.

26:01.060 --> 26:04.023
[ CHUCKLES ]

26:04.023 --> 26:06.105
BUT I THOUGHT WE WERE
THE WONDER TWINS.

26:08.027 --> 26:09.859
OH.

26:09.859 --> 26:11.450
YOU'RE SERIOUS.

26:11.450 --> 26:16.035
W-WELL...ONLY IN THE SENSE
THAT WE DO, UH,

26:16.035 --> 26:19.959
WELL, GOOD THINGS
FOR PEOPLE WHO DESERVE IT,

26:19.959 --> 26:24.664
AND...BAD THINGS
TO THOSE WHO DON'T.

26:24.664 --> 26:28.087
AND WHAT ARE YOU
ON TODAY,

26:28.087 --> 26:31.631
A MISSION OF MERCY
OR MALICE?

26:31.631 --> 26:35.805
HOW DOES..."MERCIFUL MALICE"
SUIT YOU?

26:35.805 --> 26:39.098
LIKE LA PERLA.

26:41.721 --> 26:44.273
MAYBE I CAN HELP.

26:44.273 --> 26:47.987
HM.

26:47.987 --> 26:51.150
[ GRUNTING ]

26:54.654 --> 26:56.615
EMILY!

26:56.615 --> 26:57.947
TRAINING FOR A MUD RUN?

26:57.947 --> 27:02.161
I'D TELL YOU,
BUT I'D HAVE TO KILL YOU.

27:04.123 --> 27:07.246
AND I'D LIKE
TO KEEP YOU AROUND...

27:07.246 --> 27:09.749
FOR YOUR WITTY REPARTEE.

27:09.749 --> 27:10.960
OH, WELL,
NOW THE PRESSURE'S ON.

27:10.960 --> 27:12.091
[ CHUCKLES ]
 LET ME ASK YOU SOMETHING.

27:12.091 --> 27:13.382
DID YOU SEE JACK TODAY?

27:13.382 --> 27:14.884
YEAH.

27:14.884 --> 27:16.846
DID YOU GET THE SENSE
THAT HE KNOWS ABOUT US?

27:16.846 --> 27:19.929
NOT THAT THERE'S AN "US,"
PER SE, BUT...

27:19.929 --> 27:22.101
IT DIDN'T COME UP.
WHY?

27:22.101 --> 27:25.224
I-I-I SAW HIM AT THE STATION
HOUSE THIS MORNING.

27:25.224 --> 27:26.105
HE MADE A COMMENT

27:26.105 --> 27:28.647
ABOUT US TRAVELING
IN THE SAME CIRCLES.

27:28.647 --> 27:31.530
WELL, MAYBE I'M READING
TOO MUCH INTO IT.

27:31.530 --> 27:33.072
SO, YOU GOT PLANS TONIGHT?

27:33.072 --> 27:35.324
UM, YEAH, ACTUALLY.

27:35.324 --> 27:37.196
I'D ASK WHAT,
BUT I WOULDN'T WANT YOU

27:37.196 --> 27:39.618
TO HAVE TO KILL ME
IN FRONT OF ALL THESE PEOPLE.

27:51.500 --> 27:53.462
HOW'D IT GO
WITH JACK?

27:53.462 --> 27:55.755
HE'S A GOOD MAN

27:55.755 --> 27:57.717
WHO UNFORTUNATELY IS FRIENDS
WITH THE WRONG PERSON.

27:57.717 --> 28:00.469
BUT HE TRIED
TO PLAY ME

28:00.469 --> 28:02.601
JUST LIKE
YOU PLAYED NOLAN.

28:02.601 --> 28:04.143
YOU'RE BETTER AT IT.

28:04.143 --> 28:06.605
SO WE'RE STILL
MOVING FORWARD, THEN?

28:06.605 --> 28:09.148
CALL THE FBI.

28:09.148 --> 28:10.229
I WANT THEM TO BE THERE

28:10.229 --> 28:12.271
TO SPOIL ALL OF HER FUN.

28:12.271 --> 28:14.073
TONIGHT, EMILY THORNE

28:14.073 --> 28:17.406
WILL FINALLY GET
WHAT SHE DESERVES.

28:23.372 --> 28:25.164
[ HORN HONKS IN DISTANCE ]

28:25.164 --> 28:26.285
I'M IN POSITION.

28:26.285 --> 28:27.997
AND MISSION EM-POSSIBLE IS A GO.

28:27.997 --> 28:31.540
ALL RIGHT,
I'M DEACTIVATING THE ALARM

28:31.540 --> 28:33.132
on the northeast corner.

28:36.135 --> 28:38.137
EMS?

28:38.137 --> 28:39.839
EMS?

28:39.839 --> 28:41.300
[ PANTING ]

28:41.300 --> 28:44.603
I'M GOOD.

28:44.603 --> 28:45.895
ALL RIGHT.

28:45.895 --> 28:47.476
YOU'RE MAKING MY PALMS SWEAT.

28:47.476 --> 28:49.438
[ KEYS CLACKING ]

28:49.438 --> 28:50.439
[ BEEPS ]

28:50.439 --> 28:51.811
YOU'RE CLEAR.

28:51.811 --> 28:54.153
I'M GOING IN.

29:01.490 --> 29:03.242
[ KEYS CLACKING ]

29:03.242 --> 29:04.413
[ BEEPS ]

29:04.413 --> 29:05.995
AND NORTH HALLWAY'S CLEAR.

29:16.635 --> 29:18.547
Man: STOP RIGHT THERE!

29:18.547 --> 29:20.089
OH, MY GOODNESS.

29:20.089 --> 29:21.801
THIS ISN'T SOUL CYCLE.

29:21.801 --> 29:23.472
LOUISE?!
 [ SCOFFS ]

29:23.472 --> 29:26.145
YOU KNOW HER?
 GOSH DARN IT,
I COULD HAVE SWORN

29:26.145 --> 29:28.097
JACK SAID THE GYM WAS
ON THE EIGHTH FLOOR.

29:28.097 --> 29:30.389
JACK SENT YOU HERE?

29:30.389 --> 29:31.941
OR WAS IT EIGHTH AVENUE?

29:31.941 --> 29:34.854
YOU KNOW, I AM SO TERRIBLE
WITH DIRECTIONS.

29:34.854 --> 29:36.655
I'M SO SORRY TO INTERRUPT.
[ GIGGLES ]

29:36.655 --> 29:38.027
Lin: UM, MA'AM?
 YES?

29:38.027 --> 29:39.528
AGENT WESTGATE HERE
IS GONNA NEED TO ASK YOU

29:39.528 --> 29:41.030
A FEW QUESTIONS
BEFORE YOU GO.

29:41.030 --> 29:44.403
OH. MY PLEASURE.
 THIS WAY, MA'AM.

29:46.365 --> 29:48.868
OKAY, SO, A FEW QUESTIONS,
AND THEN WHAT?

29:48.868 --> 29:50.079
WELL, IF THERE'S
NOTHING SUSPICIOUS,

29:50.079 --> 29:52.872
THEN SHE'S FREE TO GO --
STANDARD OPERATING PROCEDURE.

29:52.872 --> 29:54.213
SHE'S GOING TO LIE.

29:54.213 --> 29:56.085
THAT WOMAN
IS WORKING WITH THEM!

29:56.085 --> 29:58.417
WHO'S "THEM"?

30:00.379 --> 30:01.841
I'LL SHOW YOU.

30:05.474 --> 30:07.136
[ BEEPS ]

30:16.525 --> 30:18.988
I DON'T KNOW WHAT YOU'RE
UP TO, MS. LeMARCHAL,

30:18.988 --> 30:21.700
BUT THIS IS CLEARLY
A WASTE OF AGENCY RESOURCES.

30:21.700 --> 30:24.994
GOOD NIGHT, MA'AM.

30:28.998 --> 30:30.289
Heather: ARE YOU SURE
YOU WANT TO PART

30:30.289 --> 30:31.710
WITH YOUR HUSBAND'S
CUBAN CIGARS?

30:31.710 --> 30:34.123
KNOWING YOURS
WOULD ENJOY THEM

30:34.123 --> 30:35.504
IS ALL THAT MATTERS.

30:35.504 --> 30:37.626
IT'S WHAT TEDDY
WOULD'VE WANTED.

30:37.626 --> 30:40.299
WELL, THEN...TO TEDDY.

30:40.299 --> 30:42.011
TO TEDDY.

30:42.011 --> 30:44.053
[ CHUCKLES ]
 Man: EXCUSE ME, ARE YOU

30:44.053 --> 30:45.514
THE NATALIE WATERS
WITH THE STICKLEY CHAIRS?

30:45.514 --> 30:47.596
I AM.

30:47.596 --> 30:49.228
CONSIDER YOURSELF SERVED.

30:54.393 --> 30:56.475
WHAT IS IT?

30:56.475 --> 31:00.439
TEDDY'S WILL
IS BEING CONTESTED.

31:04.243 --> 31:07.156
DOES THIS MEAN
I'M NOT GETTING THE CIGARS?

31:10.789 --> 31:12.121
YOU DIDN'T THINK
I WAS GOING TO ALLOW YOU

31:12.121 --> 31:14.873
TO DUPE MY FATHER-IN-LAW
AND LIE TO HIS HEIR, DID YOU?

31:14.873 --> 31:17.296
I LOVED HIM.

31:17.296 --> 31:20.669
WHAT EXACTLY
DID YOU LOVE MOST,

31:20.669 --> 31:22.301
THE FACT THAT HE
WAS WORTH MILLIONS,

31:22.301 --> 31:24.003
OR THAT HE WAS
ON DEATH'S DOORSTEP?

31:24.003 --> 31:25.174
I THINK IT WAS BOTH.

31:25.174 --> 31:26.595
YOU HAVE NO IDEA
WHAT YOU'RE TALKING ABOUT.

31:26.595 --> 31:27.886
DON'T I?

31:27.886 --> 31:30.139
I'VE KNOWN WOMEN LIKE YOU.

31:30.139 --> 31:31.931
IN FACT, I'VE BEEN ACCUSED
OF BEING A WOMAN LIKE YOU.

31:31.931 --> 31:34.013
SO YOU DON'T FOOL ME
FOR A SECOND.

31:34.013 --> 31:36.605
WHEN I STARTED WORKING
FOR TEDDY,

31:36.605 --> 31:38.397
MY LIFE
WAS FALLING APART.

31:38.397 --> 31:40.569
I WAS IN A HORRIBLE
MARRIAGE.

31:40.569 --> 31:41.900
WELL, SURE.

31:41.900 --> 31:43.022
YOU WERE POOR.

31:43.022 --> 31:44.323
AND EVERY DAY,

31:44.323 --> 31:47.116
WHEN I ARRIVED TO WORK,
TEDDY, DESPITE HIS ILLNESS,

31:47.116 --> 31:50.329
SHOWED ME MORE KINDNESS
THAN ANYONE EVER HAS.

31:50.329 --> 31:53.122
I KNOW
IT MAY BE DIFFICULT

31:53.122 --> 31:56.125
FOR SMALL-MINDED PEOPLE
TO COMPREHEND,

31:56.125 --> 31:57.586
BUT WE FELL IN LOVE.

31:57.586 --> 31:58.707
MM-HMM.

31:58.707 --> 32:00.419
SO, WHILE OUR MARRIAGE
MAY HAVE BEEN BRIEF,

32:00.419 --> 32:03.752
OUR LOVE, NEVERTHELESS,
WAS REAL.

32:03.752 --> 32:07.386
[ Voice breaking ] AND IF
GIVING YOU HIS ENTIRE ESTATE

32:07.386 --> 32:09.808
WOULD BRING HIM BACK,
I WOULD.

32:09.808 --> 32:11.930
WELL, WHY DON'T YOU TRY?

32:11.930 --> 32:13.262
YOU NEVER KNOW.

32:13.262 --> 32:16.515
TEDDY SAVED MY LIFE,

32:16.515 --> 32:19.058
AND I WOULD DO
ANYTHING FOR HIM.

32:19.058 --> 32:21.190
AND THAT INCLUDES
PROTECTING HIS FORTUNE

32:21.190 --> 32:24.443
FROM THE LIKES OF YOU.

32:39.038 --> 32:41.750
TRYING TO GET ME ON A B&E?

32:41.750 --> 32:45.084
WAS THAT THE BEST
YOU COULD DO?

32:45.084 --> 32:47.296
SHOULD'VE BROUGHT
YOUR FBI PALS UP HERE,

32:47.296 --> 32:50.469
BECAUSE I BOTH BROKE
AND ENTERED.

32:50.469 --> 32:51.850
NICE TRY, THOUGH.

32:51.850 --> 32:53.972
I DON'T KNOW WHAT
YOU'RE TALKING ABOUT.

32:53.972 --> 32:55.394
[ CHUCKLES ]

32:55.394 --> 32:57.306
A WORD OF ADVICE --

32:57.306 --> 32:59.018
IF YOU'RE GONNA KEEP
COMING AT ME,

32:59.018 --> 33:01.730
YOU'RE GONNA HAVE TO BE
A HELL OF A LOT SMARTER.

33:01.730 --> 33:04.233
YOU THINK
YOU'RE INVINCIBLE.

33:04.233 --> 33:05.774
NOT INVINCIBLE.

33:05.774 --> 33:09.108
JUST...BETTER.

33:09.108 --> 33:13.112
I WILL FIND
YOUR WEAK SPOT.

33:13.112 --> 33:15.414
LET ME SAVE YOU THE TROUBLE.

33:15.414 --> 33:19.078
I DON'T HAVE ONE.

33:19.078 --> 33:21.960
OH, AND, UH, BY THE WAY...

33:21.960 --> 33:24.213
NICE BRACELET.

33:58.287 --> 34:01.160
OH, NO!

34:01.160 --> 34:03.041
AAH! AAH! AAH!

34:15.934 --> 34:19.348
HEY, NATALIE?

34:19.348 --> 34:20.438
HEY.

34:20.438 --> 34:22.020
WHAT DO YOU THINK?

34:22.020 --> 34:24.353
HI. I THINK I OWE YOU
AN APOLOGY.

34:24.353 --> 34:25.444
[ CHUCKLES ]

34:25.444 --> 34:26.735
IT APPEARS I GAVE YOU

34:26.735 --> 34:28.187
THE FIRST BOAT EVER MADE.

34:28.187 --> 34:29.237
[ BOTH CHUCKLE ]

34:29.237 --> 34:30.188
WELL, 15 YEARS, UH,

34:30.188 --> 34:32.360
SITTING IN A HARBOR
WILL DO THAT.

34:32.360 --> 34:35.694
BUT I WANTED A PROJECT,
SO NO APOLOGY NECESSARY.

34:35.694 --> 34:38.157
WELL, THEN,
YOU'RE WELCOME.

34:38.157 --> 34:39.328
[ CHUCKLES ]

34:42.000 --> 34:43.001
HAVE A GOOD NIGHT.

34:45.123 --> 34:48.877
IS IT TRUE...
THAT YOU'RE A GRAYSON?

34:51.089 --> 34:52.880
KNOWING YOUR HISTORY,

34:52.880 --> 34:56.135
IT DIDN'T SEEM LIKE
A GOOD THING TO LEAD WITH.

34:56.135 --> 34:58.847
YOU MAY HAVE THOUGHT I HAD
AN ULTERIOR MOTIVE.

34:58.847 --> 35:02.641
SHOULD I BE WORRIED
THERE'S A CRACK IN THE HULL?

35:02.641 --> 35:03.812
[ LAUGHS ]

35:03.812 --> 35:04.983
FULL DISCLOSURE --

35:04.983 --> 35:07.105
THE ONLY REASON
I WOULD SINK THIS SHIP

35:07.105 --> 35:09.188
IS IF VICTORIA GRAYSON
WERE ON IT.

35:10.649 --> 35:12.531
OH, WOW, OH.

35:12.531 --> 35:13.902
I'M SORRY.

35:13.902 --> 35:16.114
YOU GUYS AREN'T STILL...

35:16.114 --> 35:17.075
NO, NO, WE'VE MOVED ON.

35:17.075 --> 35:18.867
OKAY.
[ CHUCKLES ]

35:18.867 --> 35:21.660
W-- BESIDES,
I WOULD NEVER LET

35:21.660 --> 35:24.413
ALL YOUR HARD WORK
TO HONOR TEDDY GO TO WASTE.

35:24.413 --> 35:26.124
WELL, IF YOU CALL
LISTENING TO THE CUBS GAME

35:26.124 --> 35:27.666
AND DRINKING BEER WORKING,
THEN...

35:27.666 --> 35:29.458
CONSIDERING HOW THEY'VE
BEEN PLAYING LATELY,

35:29.458 --> 35:30.629
IT DOES FEEL LIKE A JOB,

35:30.629 --> 35:31.800
SO I GUESS IT QUALIFIES.

35:31.800 --> 35:33.172
WELL, THEY'RE DOWN EIGHT
IN THE SECOND, SO...

35:33.172 --> 35:34.173
WELL...

35:34.173 --> 35:35.594
WAIT,
DO YOU WANT TO JOIN?

35:40.098 --> 35:42.060
WHAT'S MISERY WITHOUT
A LITTLE COMPANY, RIGHT?

35:42.060 --> 35:45.184
[ CHUCKLES ]

35:45.184 --> 35:47.105
SO THIS LITTLE DOOHICKEY

35:47.105 --> 35:49.688
ERASED MARGAUX'S
ENTIRE COMPUTER?

35:49.688 --> 35:51.940
WORKED LIKE A CHARM.

35:51.940 --> 35:55.234
UH, NOW LET'S PUT THAT AWAY
BEFORE YOU DO THE SAME TO MINE.

35:55.234 --> 35:57.616
WELL, THANK YOU
FOR TRUSTING ME.

35:57.616 --> 35:58.617
I DON'T.

35:58.617 --> 35:59.618
SERIOUSLY.

35:59.618 --> 36:01.450
LET'S PUT THAT AWAY.

36:03.041 --> 36:05.083
YOU KNOW, I KNOW
I DIDN'T DO MUCH, BUT...

36:05.083 --> 36:09.378
IT WAS NICE
TO FEEL INCLUDED.

36:12.251 --> 36:14.673
I AM SO SORRY
I DIDN'T SEE IT SOONER.

36:14.673 --> 36:16.054
SEE WHAT?

36:18.757 --> 36:22.140
HOW MUCH WE'RE ALIKE.

36:22.140 --> 36:26.144
I MEAN, I S-SPENT MOST
OF MY LIFE AS AN OUTSIDER,

36:26.144 --> 36:29.478
AND IT [SIGHS]
IT FELT AWFUL.

36:29.478 --> 36:31.360
BUT THEN EMILY SHOWED UP

36:31.360 --> 36:33.071
AND TRUSTED ME
TO BE HER PARTNER,

36:33.071 --> 36:36.154
AND...MY LIFE CHANGED.

36:36.154 --> 36:40.028
SO, WHILE OUR WEDDING
WAS STRATEGIC...

36:40.028 --> 36:44.373
I DID PROMISE
TO BE THERE FOR YOU.

36:44.373 --> 36:47.496
I'M SO SORRY
THAT I WASN'T.

36:53.502 --> 36:54.713
PERDONAMI?

36:54.713 --> 36:56.675
YES.

37:02.180 --> 37:03.472
[ ELEVATOR BELL DINGS ]

37:05.474 --> 37:07.606
YOU SERVED NATALIE
THE PAPERS?

37:07.606 --> 37:09.898
WELL, ISN'T THAT WHY
YOU HAD THEM DRAWN UP?

37:09.898 --> 37:11.270
YOU COMPLETELY
JUMPED THE GUN.

37:11.270 --> 37:13.111
NOW HER PUBLIC DECLARATION'S
ALL OVER TMI.

37:13.111 --> 37:14.613
SHE'S BECOME
THE ANTI-ANNA NICOLE.

37:14.613 --> 37:16.405
I HELPED YOU.
 HOW, BY NOT GIVING ME

37:16.405 --> 37:18.277
SUFFICIENT TIME
TO BUILD MY CASE?

37:18.277 --> 37:20.028
BY GETTING HER
TO DECLARE HER LOVE

37:20.028 --> 37:22.030
PUBLICLY AND ON THE RECORD.

37:22.030 --> 37:23.572
WE NOW HAVE
A NARRATIVE TO RUIN.

37:23.572 --> 37:24.743
HOW?

37:24.743 --> 37:25.744
DID YOU SEE HER?

37:25.744 --> 37:27.706
SHE WAS...
EMOTIONAL AND SINCERE.

37:35.714 --> 37:37.426
[ Voice breaking ]
I'M SORRY.

37:37.426 --> 37:40.048
YOU'RE RIGHT.

37:40.048 --> 37:42.180
I'VE JUST GONE THROUGH
SO MUCH LATELY, AND...

37:42.180 --> 37:45.434
I-I WANTED TO FIND
SOME WAY TO HELP.

37:45.434 --> 37:47.386
IT'S OKAY, VICTORIA.

37:47.386 --> 37:49.518
DON'T BEAT YOURSELF UP
ABOUT IT.

37:51.940 --> 37:54.983
EMOTION AND SINCERITY
CAN BE FAKED. PLEASE.

37:54.983 --> 37:57.105
[ Chuckling ]
POINT MADE.

37:57.105 --> 37:58.657
NATALIE'S SOB STORY

37:58.657 --> 38:02.741
NOW EXISTS FOR US TO DISMANTLE
PIECE BY PIECE.

38:02.741 --> 38:05.324
EVEN IF THAT MEANS
FABRICATING INFORMATION?

38:05.324 --> 38:06.325
TALKING LIKE A LAWYER...

38:06.325 --> 38:09.207
BUT THINKING
LIKE A POLITICIAN.

38:09.207 --> 38:11.249
I TRULY AM
THE BEST OF BOTH WORLDS.

38:11.249 --> 38:13.081
AND IN MY SHORT TIME HERE,

38:13.081 --> 38:15.043
I CAN SEE THAT HONESTY
DOES NOT GET YOU VERY FAR,

38:15.043 --> 38:17.876
SO WHO AM I TO BREAK
WITH TRADITION?

38:17.876 --> 38:19.798
HEAR, HEAR.

38:22.881 --> 38:24.723
[ SIREN WAILING IN DISTANCE ]

38:31.930 --> 38:33.352
MISS LeMARCHAL.

38:33.352 --> 38:35.564
IS EVERYTHING OKAY?

38:35.564 --> 38:38.196
YOU TELL ME.

38:38.196 --> 38:40.238
THAT'S APRIL.

38:40.238 --> 38:41.440
ARE YOU LOOKING
FOR MY EX-WIFE?

38:41.440 --> 38:42.491
NO.

38:42.491 --> 38:45.153
NO, I FOUND HER.

38:47.115 --> 38:48.326
YOU KNOW WHERE SHE IS?

38:48.326 --> 38:50.288
WHICH MAKES ONE OF US.

38:50.288 --> 38:52.871
AND IF YOU DON'T DO
AS I ASK,

38:52.871 --> 38:54.122
I COULD LET ANOTHER PERSON

38:54.122 --> 38:56.254
KNOW WHERE SHE IS --

38:56.254 --> 38:57.666
SOMEONE WHO WANTS
TO FIND HER

38:57.666 --> 39:00.629
FOR A COMPLETELY
DIFFERENT REASON.

39:04.012 --> 39:05.424
WHAT DO YOU WANT?

39:19.398 --> 39:20.649
IT WORKED.

39:20.649 --> 39:21.650
YOU'RE IN THE CLEAR.

39:21.650 --> 39:23.482
[ EXHALES DEEPLY ]

39:23.482 --> 39:25.153
THANKS.

39:25.153 --> 39:27.245
THANK YOU.

39:27.245 --> 39:29.538
WE ALL DID OUR PART.

39:31.870 --> 39:34.493
I KNOW
ABOUT YOU AND BEN.

39:39.047 --> 39:40.959
AND?

39:40.959 --> 39:43.842
AND YOU HAVE TO KNOW...

39:43.842 --> 39:46.134
THAT THERE'S SOMEONE
OUT THERE

39:46.134 --> 39:47.926
WHO'S A BETTER FIT
FOR YOU.

39:55.063 --> 39:57.315
I REALIZE THAT MY TIMING
IS TERRIBLE.

39:57.315 --> 39:58.607
[ CHUCKLES ]

39:58.607 --> 39:59.778
I GET THAT.

39:59.778 --> 40:01.520
BUT...AFTER AIDEN...

40:01.520 --> 40:03.942
I KNOW WHAT IT MEANS

40:03.942 --> 40:05.193
TO LOSE SOMEONE,
AND I WAS --

40:05.193 --> 40:07.025
I WAS TRYING
TO GIVE YOU SPACE.

40:07.025 --> 40:08.326
SO YOU'RE DOING THIS NOW

40:08.326 --> 40:10.158
BECAUSE YOU THINK
I'VE MOVED ON WITH BEN?

40:10.158 --> 40:11.199
JACK --
 I'M DOING THIS NOW

40:11.199 --> 40:13.582
BECAUSE I CAN'T WATCH YOU
BE WITH ANYONE ELSE,

40:13.582 --> 40:15.083
BECAUSE FOR ONCE,

40:15.083 --> 40:17.536
WE ARE BOTH IN A PLACE
TO MAYBE START A RELATIONSHIP,

40:17.536 --> 40:19.167
AND AFTER EVERYTHING
THAT WE'VE BEEN THROUGH,

40:19.167 --> 40:21.129
AND AT A TIME WHEN I DON'T KNOW
WHAT THE FUTURE HOLDS,

40:21.129 --> 40:24.923
I HAVE ONE CERTAINTY
IN MY LIFE, EMILY -- ONE.

40:24.923 --> 40:28.637
AND THAT IS
HOW I FEEL ABOUT YOU.

40:30.308 --> 40:34.182
IT'S ALWAYS BEEN YOU...

40:34.182 --> 40:36.394
FROM THE MOMENT
SAMMY RAN UP TO YOU THAT DAY.

40:36.394 --> 40:38.977
[ CHUCKLES ]

40:45.153 --> 40:46.324
I DON'T KNOW WHAT TO SAY.

40:46.324 --> 40:50.489
THINGS BETWEEN US, JACK,

40:50.489 --> 40:52.030
THEY'RE...

40:52.030 --> 40:54.072
THEY'RE MESSY.

40:56.625 --> 40:58.076
LIFE IS MESSY.

41:00.078 --> 41:04.042
BUT...YOU FIND A WAY.

41:07.756 --> 41:11.349
[ BREATHES DEEPLY ]

41:18.146 --> 41:21.019
YOU HAVE DONE AND SACRIFICED
SO MUCH FOR ME.

41:22.731 --> 41:25.233
YOU KNOW HOW MUCH
I CARE ABOUT YOU.

41:27.656 --> 41:30.068
BUT...

41:32.741 --> 41:34.202
BUT WHAT?

41:39.998 --> 41:42.921
I CAN'T, JACK.

41:42.921 --> 41:45.173
I'M SORRY.

41:54.092 --> 41:56.014
I'M NOT GONNA WAIT AROUND.
